<eesti>&Uuml;li&otilde;pilaskond ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilasesindus </eesti>
<inglise>Student Body and Student Council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;likooli &uuml;li&otilde;pilased moodustavad &uuml;he &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The students of a university form the Student Body. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;li&otilde;pilaskond on institutsioon, mis teostab &uuml;li&otilde;pilaste &otilde;igust omavalitsusele - otsustada ja korraldada iseseisvalt, koosk&otilde;las seaduse ja seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega, &uuml;li&otilde;pilaselu k&uuml;simusi, l&auml;htudes &uuml;li&otilde;pilaste huvidest, vajadustest, &otilde;igustest ning kohustustest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Student Body is an institution which exercises the right of students to self-government - to decide and manage independently, pursuant to law and legislation issued on the basis thereof, the issues of student life based on the interests, needs, rights and obligations of students. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonnal on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Student Bodies have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) moodustada teiste &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskondadega liite ja organisatsioone &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras; </eesti>
<inglise>1) form associations and organisations with other Student Bodies on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided by legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) astuda vastavate rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonide liikmeks v&otilde;i arendada nendega koost&ouml;&ouml;d; </eesti>
<inglise>2) become members of the corresponding international organisations or develop co-operation with such organisation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valida oma esindajaid &uuml;likooli n&otilde;ukogusse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) elect their representatives to the board of the university; </inglise>
<eesti>4) otsustada ja korraldada k&otilde;iki muid &uuml;li&otilde;pilaselu k&uuml;simusi, mis seaduse ja seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kuuluvad &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna p&auml;devusse ning mis ei ole samadel alustel antud kellegi teise otsustada ja korraldada. </eesti>
<inglise>4) decide and manage all other issues of student life which pursuant to law and legislation issued on the basis thereof are within the competence of a Student Body and which on the same grounds have not been transferred to any other person to decide or manage. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonnal on p&otilde;hikiri, kus s&auml;testatakse &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna esindus- ja t&auml;itevorganite moodustamise kord, nende &otilde;igused, kohustused ja vastutus ning t&ouml;&ouml;kord. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Student Bodies have statutes which provide the procedure for the formation of students' representative and executive bodies, and for the rights, obligations, liability and rules of procedure thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna p&otilde;hikirja v&otilde;tab vastu ja esitab n&otilde;ukogule kinnitamiseks &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskond &uuml;likooli p&otilde;hikirjas s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A Student Body shall adopt the statutes of the Student Body and submit the statutes to the board for approval pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the university. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ukogu kinnitab &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna p&otilde;hikirja, kui see vastab seadustele, seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidele ja rahvusvaheliselt tunnustatud demokraatlikele p&otilde;him&otilde;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise>The board shall approve the statutes of the Student Body if the statutes comply with law, legislation issued on the basis of law and internationally recognised democratic principles. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna vastutav ja korraldav esindusorgan on demokraatlikult valitud &uuml;li&otilde;pilasesindus, mille valimise &otilde;igus on k&otilde;ikidel &uuml;likooli &uuml;li&otilde;pilastel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The responsible representative body which governs a Student Body is the democratically elected Student Council which all the students of the university have the right to elect. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;li&otilde;pilasesindus ja tema poolt vastavalt &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna p&otilde;hikirjale moodustatud &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna t&auml;itevorganid esindavad &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonda suhetes &uuml;likooliga, Eesti ja rahvusvaheliste &uuml;henduste, asutuste ja isikutega. </eesti>
<inglise>A Student Council and the executive bodies of a Student Body formed by the Student Council pursuant to the statutes of the Student Body shall represent the Student Body in relations with the university, Estonian and international organisations, agencies and persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Esimese &uuml;li&otilde;pilasesinduse valimiseeskirja kinnitab ning valimised korraldab rektor demokraatlikest p&otilde;him&otilde;tetest l&auml;htudes. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The rector shall approve the election rules and organise the elections of the first Student Council based on democratic principles. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) &Uuml;li&otilde;pilasesindus k&auml;sutab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 51 l&otilde;ikes 5 nimetatud vahendeid iseseisvalt rektori antud volituse alusel ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilaskonna kehtestatud korras." </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A Student Council shall control the funds specified in subsection 51 (5) of this Act independently on the basis of an authorisation issued by the rector and pursuant to the procedure established by the Student Body." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
